                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1301">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/46.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Vice
                        Consul <persName type="to">Stadden</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 21, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your January 19. You will make formal protest against attempt to impose forced
                    loan upon American citizens. If, however, authorities persist in attempt to
                    collect, you will advise Americans to pay under protest, making such protest a
                    matter of record if possible and to obtain receipts.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
